  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Feature\r\n\r\n*Summary*: \"There are no messages in this chat yet\" appears every time a public chat is loading no matter if it has messages or not. If there are historical messages, the empty state hides and messages are shown. In the meantime, the screen is lagging trying to render the messages. A solution for it would be to always show a spinner before messages are fetched and only show the empty state if there are no messages in the network.  \r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7532782/39912745-fdd8b454-54ff-11e8-9b3d-76c9dc7cd928.png\" width=\"200\">\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nSee a spinner when messages are being fetched. Then show empty state if there are no messages. This should work for every chat (public, group, 1-1) when fetching first messages. \r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nEmpty state is always shown upfront. Then, after couple of seconds it hides and messages appear.\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Join #status public chat\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: nightly, May 11\r\n* Operating System: Android, iOS",
